OL,3,CCharity skinny dip banned due to 1950s
OL,4,Cdecency law
OL,6,FThe law states: "No person shall, on
OL,7,Fany beach, behave or be clothed in any
OL,8,Fmanner reasonably likely to offend
OL,9,Fpublic decency."
OL,11,FHowever, this legislation dates back
OL,12,Fto the 1950s, whereas the UK and
OL,13,FGuernsey law permits certain public
OL,14,Fnudity that is not considered
OL,15,F"outrageous".
OL,17,FIslander Ross Mantle believes that
OL,18,FJersey is "behind the times".
